  "notes": [
    "This paper presents a cross-sectional study evaluating medical treatment approaches for Cushing's disease across nine international Pituitary Tumors Centers of Excellence (PTCOEs).",
    "The study focuses on real-world clinical practice data for medical management of Cushing's disease, including usage rates and biochemical control rates for various medications.",
    "Key findings include ketoconazole being the most frequently used drug (26.5% usage rate) with 76% biochemical control rate, and overall median control rate of 75% for all medical treatments."
  ]
